## 🎯 Core Vision

**One-line pitch:**
> "The office simulation game that finally *gets* what it's actually like to work in a company — and lets you run one."

**Core fantasy (all four must coexist):**
- Be the CEO who builds an empire from nothing
- Watch your team's personalities and dynamics play out like a simulation
- Make strategic decisions that beat your competitors
- Design and grow your office space floor by floor

**Hidden educational goal:**
- Players learn how an NGO/corporate office actually operates
- Understand each role's challenges: Procurement, Operations, Secretary, Management
- Experience the donor-dependency model of NGO funding — no income generation, rely on donors and HQ annual funding
- Cross-team cooperation is required to succeed (no single team can win alone)

**The Kairosoft DNA we keep:**
- Pixel art aesthetic — charming, not realistic
- 30 Framerate
- Stats bars that go up as you improve
- Watch employees visually doing their jobs (idle animations, walking to rooms)
- Satisfying number growth loop
- Chill pace — player sets direction, game runs itself
- Facility combos reward spatial planning

**What makes Pocket Office different from Kairosoft:**
- Employees have complex, *relatable* personalities (office archetypes everyone recognizes)
- Train employees using Corporate Points earned from working
- Group training bonuses — certain personality/role combinations train better together
- Random events pulled directly from real office life
- Office politics and drama between employees — relationships that shift over time
- Work-life balance as a core mechanic (burnout, vacation, morale)
- 5-year structured campaign with annual evaluations + sandbox after ending
- **Fever Mode** — when Office Motivation hits 100%, all stats double for 5 minutes
- Task-Stat matching — specific stats make employees better at specific task types
- Donor system teaches NGO funding model — win donors via Research to unlock projects and new recruits

