## 🕹️ Core Game Loop

```
Hire staff → Assign to projects → Earn Corporate Points + Revenue
     ↑                                           ↓
Upgrade office ←── Spend Corp Points ←── Win Donors → More Projects
```

**Time system:**
- 1 month = 8 ticks, each tick = 60 seconds real time
- 1 year = ~96 minutes real time (12 months x 8 ticks x 60s)
- 5-year campaign = ~8 hours total playtime
- Each tick simulates a workday (08:00–16:00 clock display)
- Project progress, OT penalties, and motivation changes apply once per tick

**Tick loop (per tick = 60 real seconds):**
1. Time advances automatically (chill — player doesn't need to watch every second but would love to anyway in case there is a pop-up)
2. Employees work on assigned projects; productivity determined by stats + office buffs
3. Employees walk around and use facilities (5–10 seconds per facility, then move on)
4. Random events fire occasionally — player makes a choice
5. Morale/burnout ticks in background for each employee

**Monthly loop:**
- Pay salaries + rent
- New project contracts arrive
- Review team performance

**Annual loop (KEY MECHANIC):**
- Year-end evaluation — scored across 5 categories (Revenue, Reputation, Team Motivation, Office Quality, Project Completion Rate)
- Compared against 3–5 AI competitor companies
- Year 5 = Final Evaluation = Campaign win condition

---

## 🏆 Win Condition & Game Structure

**Campaign mode (5 years):**
- Each year has an annual evaluation
- Year 5 final evaluation determines ranking vs. all competitors
- **Win = #1 ranked company after Year 5**
- Multiple outcomes possible based on strategy (revenue-focused vs reputation-focused vs employee-focused)
- After campaign ends → **Sandbox mode unlocks** (keep playing forever, no evaluation pressure)

**Prestige system (post-campaign):**
- After completing a campaign, player can "Prestige"
- Reset company but keep small permanent bonuses (e.g., legendary employee, +5% to all stats, extra starting cash)
- Encourages multiple playthroughs with different strategies

**Multiple playthrough variety:**
- Different random event seeds each run
- Random employee pool means different team dynamics every time
- Different competitor behaviors keep competition fresh

