## 👤 Employee System (Most Important Differentiator)

### Personality Archetypes
These should feel like people players have *actually worked with*:

| Personality | Behavior in-game | Office reference |
|---|---|---|
| Workaholic | High output, burns out fast, hates vacation events | "That guy who emails at midnight" |
| Gossip | Spreads morale buffs AND debuffs, causes drama events | "The office news channel" |
| Perfectionist | Slow but high quality, conflicts with Lazy types | "Won't submit until it's perfect" |
| Lazy | Low output, high morale drain if others notice | "Always in the kitchen" |
| Team Player | Boosts nearby employees' morale | "The glue of the team" |
| Lone Wolf | High personal output, terrible team synergy | "Brilliant but impossible to work with" |
| Brown-noser | Buffs reputation when investor/client events fire | "Always in the boss's office" |
| Quiet Quitter | Looks present, produces minimum output | "Doing the bare minimum since 2022" |
| Legendary | Well respected, built themselves from ground up, high start stats | "Been through all of the problems since 2020" |

### Employee Relationships (Office Politics)
- Employees develop **relationship scores** with each other over time
- Some personality combos create **drama events** (e.g., Gossip + Perfectionist = conflict)
- Some combos create **synergy bonuses** (e.g., Team Player + anyone = +morale)
- Seating/room placement affects relationship development

### Work-Life Balance Mechanic
- **Stress meter** (0–100) per employee — rises with overwork, falls with breaks
- **Burnout state** triggers at stress 90+ — employee becomes 20% productivity, spreads negativity
- **Vacation events** reduce stress across the team
- Player must balance pushing hard on deadline projects vs. protecting team wellbeing

